abstract: Statewide recanvassing in Kentucky does not alter 83-vote margin of victory for Matt Bevin, businessman who challenged James R Comer for Republican nomination for governor.
lead_paragraph: A statewide recanvass did not change the outcome of the closely fought election for the Republican nomination for governor, regulators said.

headline.main: Kentucky: Outcome Unchanged in Governor Race
headline.print_headline: Kentucky: Outcome Unchanged in Governor Race
